# 🚀 First-Year to Advanced Software Development Roadmap 2026–2028  
**Ultra-Detailed • Step-by-Step • Placement-Ready Advanced Level**  
**For Indian CSE Students – From Intermediate Foundations to Top-Tier SDE Readiness**

You are now transitioning from **intermediate** (end of second year / early third year) to **advanced software developer** level.  
This roadmap assumes you already have:

- 500–800 DSA problems solved (350+ medium, 70+ hard)
- 8–12 deployed full-stack projects (MERN / similar, live links)
- Strong understanding of core subjects (OOP/DBMS/OS/CN)
- Git/GitHub professional (200+ commits, clean READMEs)
- Some internship applications sent or 1–2 small experiences
- CGPA ≥7.5–8.0 maintained

**Goal by end of third year / final year (2027–2028):**
- 1000–1500+ DSA problems (heavy medium/hard, company-specific patterns)
- 12–18 high-quality, production-grade projects (some with scale, real users, or open-source impact)
- 1–3 meaningful internships / freelance / open-source contributions (even short ones count massively)
- Off-campus + on-campus placements targeting 15–45+ LPA (product companies, high-paying service, scale-ups)
- Ability to clear 4–6 round interviews (coding + system design + behavioral + core subjects)

**2027–2028 India Reality Check**
- Product-based companies (Amazon, Atlassian, Flipkart, Cred, Groww, PhonePe, startups) → expect 2–3 medium-hard DSA rounds + low-level design + project deep dive
- High CTC service companies (Goldman Sachs, Deutsche Bank, JPMorgan, etc.) → advanced DSA + OS/DBMS/CN + puzzles
- Off-campus is now mainstream — LinkedIn + referrals + strong GitHub = entry
- System design basics + clean code + communication = final differentiator

